Business Brief -- Republic Waste Industries Inc.:
   Atlanta Company Will Buy
   Waste-Treatment Concern
The company said the merger more than doubles its 1991
revenue.
   Republic Waste, based in Atlanta, restated its 1991
year-end results to reflect the acquisition. The company is
now reporting net income of $4.3 million, or 22 cents a
share, on revenue of $122.9 million for 1991. The company
earlier reported net income of $2.1 million, or 13 cents a
share, on revenue of $51.6 million.
   The year includes a charge of 17 cents a share from
restructuring and a contract contingency, restated from the
previously reported charge of 19 cents a share.